"title": "5285: cures",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5285: cures",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The removing of illness or other disorder, either mental or physical. Scripture describes the curing of various diseases and conditions. It also points to humanity's area of spiritual need, its sinful condition, declaring Jesus Christ to be the only effective cure.</p>\n<h2>God's curing of illness</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job5:17-Job5:18\">JOB 5:17–5:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps30:2\">PSA 30:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps103:2-Ps103:5\">PSA 103:2–103:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps147:3\">PSA 147:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer33:6\">JER 33:6</a></p>\n<h2>Illnesses and conditions cured by Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:4-Matt11:5\">MAT 11:4–11:5</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:21-Luke7:22\">LUK 7:21–7:22</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa35:5-Isa35:6\">ISA 35:5–35:6</a></p>\n<h3>Demon-possession</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:22-Matt15:28\">MAT 15:22–15:28</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:1-Mark5:20\">MRK 5:1–5:20</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:26-Luke8:39\">LUK 8:26–8:39</a></p>\n<h3>Deafness and muteness</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:22\">MAT 12:22</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:14\">LUK 11:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:31-Mark7:37\">MRK 7:31–7:37</a></p>\n<h3>Paralysis and lameness</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:2-Matt9:8\">MAT 9:2–9:8</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:3-Mark2:12\">MRK 2:3–2:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:18-Luke5:26\">LUK 5:18–5:26</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:1-John5:14\">JHN 5:1–5:14</a></p>\n<h3>Bleeding</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:25-Mark5:34\">MRK 5:25–5:34</a></p>\n<h3>Blindness</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:22-Mark8:26\">MRK 8:22–8:26</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:1-John9:7\">JHN 9:1–9:7</a></p>\n<h3>Leprosy</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:2-Matt8:4\">MAT 8:2–8:4</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:40-Mark1:44\">MRK 1:40–1:44</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:12-Luke5:14\">LUK 5:12–5:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke17:11-Luke17:19\">LUK 17:11–17:19</a></p>\n<h2>Death itself is cured by Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:1-John11:44\">JHN 11:1–11:44</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:35-Mark5:43\">MRK 5:35–5:43</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:11-Luke7:16\">LUK 7:11–7:16</a></p>\n<h2>Illnesses and conditions cured by the apostles</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:12-Acts5:16\">ACT 5:12–5:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:1-Acts3:10\">ACT 3:1–3:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:11-Acts19:12\">ACT 19:11–19:12</a></p>\n<h2>Illnesses cured by the grace of God</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:26-Phil2:27\">PHP 2:26–2:27</a> <em>Epaphroditus, Paul's fellow-worker</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:15-Jas5:16\">JAS 5:15–5:16</a> <em>the importance of prayer in curing illness</em></p>\n<h2>Illnesses cured in the name of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:39\">MRK 9:39</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:6\">ACT 3:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:16\">ACT 3:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:10\">ACT 4:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:30\">ACT 4:30</a></p>\n<h2>Humanity's sinfulness cured by Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>Sinfulness affects all humanity</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:23\">ROM 3:23</a></p>\n<h3>Prophecy of healing through Jesus Christ's death</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:5\">ISA 53:5</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's mission to cure humanity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:12-Matt9:13\">MAT 9:12–9:13</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:17\">MRK 2:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:31\">LUK 5:31</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:10\">LUK 19:10</a></p>",
